<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="298" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,363,1039]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,305,363,390]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is distributed throughout the northern GOM from southern Florida to the Texas/ 
<collectingCountry box="[1351,1436,364,390]" name="Mexico" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Mexico</collectingCountry>
border. It inhabits estuarine and coastal waters and is commonly reported to 
<quantity box="[1000,1056,399,427]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" unit="m" value="55.0">55 m</quantity>
in depth, although NMFS SEFSC trawl surveys have documented them as deep as 
<specimenCount box="[696,760,436,463]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" type="generic">
<quantity box="[696,756,436,463]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" unit="m" value="82.0">82 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,363,1039]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,472,471,498]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">First Record in GOM.</emphasis>
Because of the similarity between 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hildebrand &amp; Schroeder" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[879,1118,473,498]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Hypanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="americanus">
<emphasis box="[879,1118,473,498]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Hypanus americanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mitchill" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[1177,1429,472,498]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Bathytoshia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="centroura">
<emphasis box="[1177,1429,472,498]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Bathytoshia centroura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is difficult to separate reports of early collections of the two species, especially considering the specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DeKay" authorityYear="1842" box="[151,233,544,570]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pastinaca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hastata">
<emphasis box="[151,233,544,570]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">hastata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or some variation thereof, was variably used for both species (see Remarks below). However, it is probable the first documentation of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hildebrand &amp; Schroeder" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[449,686,581,606]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Hypanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="americanus">
<emphasis box="[449,686,581,606]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Hypanus americanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the northern GOM in the literature (as 
<taxonomicName box="[1189,1376,580,606]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hastata">
<emphasis box="[1189,1376,580,606]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Dasyatis hastata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) was by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gudger, E. W." box="[186,352,616,642]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" pagination="176 - 177" refId="ref17742" refString="Gudger, E. W. (1913) Summary of work done on the fishes of Tortugas. Year book - Carnegie Institution of Washington, 12, 176 - 177." type="journal article" year="1913">Gudger (1913)</bibRefCitation>
who reports making observations of this species while working in the Dry 
<collectingCountry box="[1193,1294,617,643]" name="Haiti" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Tortugas</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="298" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,363,1039]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,652,678]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Rafinesque, 1818" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1818" box="[442,743,652,678]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Hypanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[442,542,653,678]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Hypanus</emphasis>
Rafinesque, 1818
</taxonomicName>
was previously considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1810" box="[1281,1379,653,678]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1281,1379,653,678]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Dasyatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until resurrected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Last, P. &amp; White, W. T. &amp; de Carvalho, M. R. &amp; Seret, B. &amp; Stehmann, M. F. W. &amp; Naylor, G. J. P." box="[317,510,688,715]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" refId="ref18676" refString="Last, P., White, W. T., de Carvalho, M. R., Seret, B., Stehmann, M. F. W. &amp; Naylor, G. J. P. (Eds.), (2016) Rays of the World. CSIRO publishing. Melbourne, 790 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / 9780643109148" type="book" year="2016">
Last 
<emphasis box="[372,428,688,714]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
based predominantly on molecular evidence. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dekay, J. E." box="[1024,1185,688,715]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" refId="ref16777" refString="Dekay, J. E. (1842) Zoology of New-York, or the New-York fauna; comprising detailed descriptions of all the animals hitherto observed within the state of New-York, with brief notices of those occasionally found near its borders, and accompanied by appropriate illustrations. Part IV. Fishes. W. &amp; A. White &amp; J. Visscheri, Albany, xv + 415 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 13735" type="book" year="1842">DeKay (1842)</bibRefCitation>
described a species of dasyatid ray, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DeKay" authorityYear="1842" box="[300,501,724,750]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pastinaca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hastata">
<emphasis box="[300,501,724,750]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Pastinaca hastata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, similar in many ways to both what is currently referred to as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hildebrand &amp; Schroeder" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[1199,1437,725,750]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Hypanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="americanus">
<emphasis box="[1199,1437,725,750]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Hypanus americanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mitchill" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[197,446,760,786]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Bathytoshia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="centroura">
<emphasis box="[197,446,760,786]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Bathytoshia centroura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. His description does not include details necessary for determining which species is actually described (
<emphasis box="[325,365,797,822]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">e.g.</emphasis>
presence or absence of dorsal fin fold), however, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hildebrand, S. F. &amp; Schroeder, W. C." box="[930,1307,796,822]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" pagination="1 - 366" refId="ref17919" refString="Hildebrand, S. F. &amp; Schroeder, W. C. (1928) Fishes of Chesapeake Bay. Bulletin of the United States Bureau of Fisheries, 43 (1), 1 - 366." type="journal article" year="1928">Hildebrand and Schroeder (1928)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DeKay" authorityYear="1842" box="[151,354,832,858]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pastinaca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hastata">
<emphasis box="[151,354,832,858]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Pastinaca hastata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
synonymous with what is now 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mitchill" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[717,968,832,858]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Bathytoshia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="centroura">
<emphasis box="[717,968,832,858]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Bathytoshia centroura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They indicated the species described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Garman, S." box="[151,322,868,894]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" pagination="65 - 72" refId="ref17345" refString="Garman, S. (1882) The American species of the genus Dasibatis. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 16, 65 - 72." type="journal article" year="1882">Garman (1882)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName box="[357,556,868,894]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasybatis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hastata">
<emphasis box="[357,556,868,894]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Dasybatis hastata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was in fact what is currently known as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hildebrand &amp; Schroeder" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[990,1226,869,894]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Hypanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="americanus">
<emphasis box="[990,1226,869,894]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Hypanus americanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but as the specific epithet 
<taxonomicName box="[234,316,904,930]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasybatis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hastata">
<emphasis box="[234,316,904,930]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">hastata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is synonymous with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mitchill" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[552,801,904,930]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Bathytoshia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="centroura">
<emphasis box="[552,801,904,930]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Bathytoshia centroura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, that name was not available. If closer inspection reveals 
<bibRefCitation author="Dekay, J. E." box="[151,330,940,966]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" refId="ref16777" refString="Dekay, J. E. (1842) Zoology of New-York, or the New-York fauna; comprising detailed descriptions of all the animals hitherto observed within the state of New-York, with brief notices of those occasionally found near its borders, and accompanied by appropriate illustrations. Part IV. Fishes. W. &amp; A. White &amp; J. Visscheri, Albany, xv + 415 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 13735" type="book" year="1842">DeKayâ€™s (1842)</bibRefCitation>
description was of what is currently called 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hildebrand &amp; Schroeder" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[816,1053,941,966]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Hypanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="americanus">
<emphasis box="[816,1053,941,966]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Hypanus americanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mitchill" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[1179,1429,940,966]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Bathytoshia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="centroura">
<emphasis box="[1179,1429,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Bathytoshia centroura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the specific epithet 
<taxonomicName box="[370,452,976,1002]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasybatis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hastata">
<emphasis box="[370,452,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">hastata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would take priority.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,363,1039]" box="[199,619,1011,1039]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,448,1011,1038]" pageId="17" pageNumber="298">Conservation Status.</emphasis>
Data Deficient
</paragraph>
